Language models (LMs) such as BERT [devlin2019bert] or GPT-3 [GPT3]
are another form of machine-based CSK, including CCSK, in principle. However, all LM knowledge is in latent form,
captured in learned values of billions of parameters. 
Knowledge cannot be made explicit; we observe it only implicitly
through the LM-based outputs in applications.
